        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:02PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 302 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Texas Creek, or 49 miles southwest of Colorado Springs, moving east
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Texas Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
